name: r-ggraph
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.0.6" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggraph
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggraph_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggraph/ggraph_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7b0ac90d834a3ce5641b4bca159d59d09607ddaab592908361b75cffb648d40a

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.2
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggforce >=0.3.1
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-ggrepel
    - r-graphlayouts >=0.5.0
    - r-gtable
    - r-igraph >=1.0.0
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-tidygraph
    - r-viridis
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-mass
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.2
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggforce >=0.3.1
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-ggrepel
    - r-graphlayouts >=0.5.0
    - r-gtable
    - r-igraph >=1.0.0
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-tidygraph
    - r-viridis

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggraph')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggraph')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/thomasp85/ggraph
  license: MIT
  summary: The grammar of graphics as implemented in ggplot2 is a poor fit for graph and network visualizations due to its reliance on tabular data input. ggraph is an extension of the ggplot2 API tailored to graph visualizations and provides the same flexible approach to building up plots layer by layer.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: ggraph

# Maintainer: Thomas Lin Pedersen <thomasp85@gmail.com>
